<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-07-09T14:50:43-07:00</updated>
<published>2017-07-09T14:50:43-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199874#p199874</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199874#p199874"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: play Gameboy Cartridge on C64 possible?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199874#p199874"><![CDATA[
Rewire the bus<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">abcdefgh -&gt; aebfcgdh</div><br />Read pixels<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">aebfcgdh<br />AEBFCGDH<br /></div><br />mask off bits<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">a0b0c0d0<br />0e0f0g0h<br />A0B0C0D0<br />0E0F0G0H<br /></div><br />shift bits<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">0a0b0c0d<br />0e0f0g0h<br />A0B0C0D0<br />E0F0G0H0<br /></div><br />OR them together and write them to video memory<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">A0B0C0D0 | 0a0b0c0d = AaBbCcDd<br />E0F0G0H0 | 0e0f0g0h = EeFfGgHh<br /></div><br />I have no idea how quickly that can be done for the 5760 bytes in the SGB frame buffer.<br /><br />But it would stretch the picture from the SGB pixel aspect ratio 8:7 to the C64 multicolor pixel aspect ratio 3:2, making everything 31% wider.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jul 09, 2017 2:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
