<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199868#p199868</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199868#p199868"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: play Gameboy Cartridge on C64 possible?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16193&amp;p=199868#p199868"><![CDATA[
To the best of my memory, the SNES packs pixels as:<br />abcdefgh ABCDEFGH<br /><br />while the VIC-2 (in 2bpp mode) packs pixels as:<br />AaBbCcDd EeFfGgHh<br /><br />so ... you might have your work cut out for you.<br /><br />It's possible (no promises) that clever rewiring of the data bus to the SGB would make it easier. (You don't <em>have</em> to connect D1 to D1, &amp;c)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Jul 09, 2017 2:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
